ber of one of UIC's oldest, yet most elite, alumni communities   There are some 12,000 AHS alumni. Each has their own story, with a common thread: understanding what is, imagining what could be, and creating what will be through professional and personal practice. Connect with AHS to be inspired, and to inspire others.       Send us an update       Submit a nomination       Request transcripts             AHS Connection  View photos of AHS alumni and friends connecting with one another at various UIC-sponsored events across the U.S.   View all photo albums        Resources   Explore the services and perks available to you as a member of our alumni community.        UIC Library   Apply for an alumni borrowing card to continue to check out materials from the library         Career services   Learn about career development resources and services available to UIC alumni         Campus recreation   Access the Student Recreation Facility, Sport & Fitness Center and Outdoor Field Complex         UIC Bookstore   Purchase UIC apparel, books and gift cards for the biggest Sparky fans in your life         UIC Alumni Association   Connect with the first alumni association dedicated to engaging UIC alumni and building pride         Illinois Connection Advocacy Network   Help gain greater federal and state support for UIC by increasing awareness of our impact           You make us proud            Arnold Lee '10 BS KINES  Chicago Bulls Assistant Athletic Trainer Arnold Lee '10 BS KINES helps the team perform at its best      Meet Arnold              Tina Esposito '97 BS HIM  Listed among the "Most Powerful Women in Healthcare IT," Tina advances technology to enhance patient-focused care      Meet Tina              Luca Badetti '15 PHD DIS  In his life and work, Luca compels us to embrace our inabilities, becoming more complete and connected human beings      Meet Luca              Brian Taliesin '13 MS HI  Brian unites people, technology and data to make life-saving vaccines more available to the children of sub-Saharan Africa      Meet Brian              Vanessa Ruiz '10 MS BVIS  In her online gallery Street Anatomy , Vanessa explores the intersection between medical illustration and contemporary art in public spaces      Meet Vanessa              Eric Meredith '12 MS NUT  Using his knowledge of nutrition, exercise and education, Eric creates comics that encourage children to eat right, stay fit and get healthy      Meet Eric            AHS Magazine       AHS Magazine is the premier publication for and about alumni and friends of the UIC College of Applied Health Sciences. Share news of your life since leaving us: new job, award, project, media mention or other notable achievement. We want to hear it!               Read the winter 2020 issue              Read the summer 2019 issue             Read the summer 2019 issue            Request a print copy       Browse our archive       Share your news            Recent News    Meet the 2020 AHS Alumni Awards recipients   Monday, February 17, 2020     Let's go far together   Thursday, February 13, 2020     One career leads to another   Monday, December 2, 2019      A gift for the future   Friday, September 13, 2019      The long journey home   Monday, March 11, 2019      All alumni news     Upcoming Events     May  15   CANCELED: Clinical Gross Anatomy of the Upper Limb and Back      This is a multi-day event that takes place May. 15 - 16     May  28   CANCELED: UIC Alumni & Recent Graduate Job Fair   Thursday      May  29   CANCELED: Clinical Gross Anatomy: Lower Limb and Pelvis      This is a multi-day event that takes place May. 29 - 30     All alumni events              Questions?   Explore the possibilities of a lifelong relationship with UIC and AHS. Contact Kristen Kepnick with questions or ideas on how to create an exceptional alumni experience.    You can contact me at:     Email  kkepnick@uic.edu      Phone  (312) 996-8219      Address  808 S. Wood St. 167 CMET (MC 518) Chicago, IL 606